msgid "Games developers are involved in the creation and production of games for personal computers, games consoles, social/online games, arcade games, tablets, mobile phones and other hand held devices. Their work involves either design (including art and animation) or programming. Games development is a fast-moving, multi-billion pound industry. The making of a game from concept to finished product can take up to three years and involve teams of up to 200 professionals. There are many stages, including creating and designing a game’s look and how it plays, animating characters and objects, creating audio, programming, localisation, testing and producing. The games developer job title covers a broad area of work and there are many specialisms within the industry. These include: quality assurance tester; programmer, with various specialisms such as network, engine, toolchain and artificial intelligence; audio engineer; artist, including concept artist, animator and 3D modeller; producer; editor; designer; special effects technician."
msgstr "游戏开发人员参与为个人电脑、游戏主机、社交/在线游戏、街机游戏、平板电脑、手机和其他手持设备创作与制作游戏。他们的工作可能涉及设计（包括美术和动画）或编程。游戏开发是一个快速发展的数十亿英镑产业。一个游戏从概念到成品可能需要长达三年，并由多达 200 名专业人员组成的团队共同完成。流程包含多个阶段，包括创建和设计游戏外观与玩法、制作角色和物体动画、创建音频、编程、本地化、测试和制作。游戏开发人员这一职位名称涵盖范围很广，行业内也有许多专业方向，包括质量保证测试员；具备网络、引擎、工具链和人工智能等专业方向的程序员；音频工程师；艺术人员，包括概念艺术家、动画师和 3D 建模师；制作人；编辑；设计师；特效技术人员。"

